How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Better than the rest!
Bought this 1 pound size bag to make sure i like it first before opting for the bigger containers. I was a long time fan of Syntha-6 but recently have been on a healthier path and after reading what the actual stuff is in Syntha, my jaw dropped. Looking for a low-carb low-sugar protein powder seemed to be a problem. Until i came across this bad boy! I purchased the Ice cream flavor despite what reviews said. I don't understand how ANYONE could complain about taste! They are crazy! Also as someone who had to use some sort of milk with my shake in the past because water tasted gross with this, i tried using water again and for the first time ever (trying to be healthy as possible) i thought it was just as amazing and HOLY HECK IT WAS JUST AS DELICIOUS!!!! i used a blender since i don't have a shaker cup plus i wanted to add ice and it turned out fantastic. No clumps. Very smooth texture. Absolutely tasty. Definitely recommend this aaaall the way!

PROS, CONS, OVERALLS
4.0 out of 5 stars OKAY FLAVOR THAT DOESN'T KEEP YOU FULL FOR LONG
Reviewed in the United States on July 22, 2021
Flavor Name: Double Rich ChocolateSize: 14 Servings (Pack of 1)Verified Purchase
PROS: I bought this size so that I can try it because I've never had a protein shake before and I didn't want to waste the product and my money. I actually liked it. It has pretty good flavor, the scoop was actually in the bag, not too high in calories, and a good amount of protein.

CONS: I tried it with a cup of soy milk right away. Not a rich double chocolate flavor that's advertised. It's more like chocolate milk. If I used less milk the flavor was better. I can't imagine what it tastes like with water. I used a blender bottle to mix the shake. Sometimes there would still be undissolved powder at the bottom even when shaking the mixture with the blender ball vigorously. Don't count on it to keep you full for long, although it's protein, it's not much and it's still a fluid that doesn't keep you full for long.

Another thing is that I tried the product with real milk, and it ended up having a sour taste. Maybe that was my taste buds because I don't like regular milk but it did taste a bit off to me.

Packaging-wise I didn't like it. Like most products now, it was halfway full, the seal was a bit hard to close at first (maybe I'm just weak).

OVERALL: As someone trying to lose weight, I will not purchase again for two reasons: 1) the flavor wasn't that great and 2)it didn't in any way shape or form control my hunger. I had the serving size (1 scoop -120 calories) and about a cup of soy milk (80 calories). I think it was just a waste of calories because fluid is so easy to digest so it doesn't keep you full which is the whole point of the protein. I might as well get those 24 - 30 grams of protein by eating REAL FOOD that will satiate my hunger for 3-4 hours instead of 1-2.

DyannLynn
3.0 out of 5 stars Vanilla Ice Cream Flavor
Reviewed in the United States on August 16, 2019
Flavor Name: Vanilla Ice CreamSize: 1 Pound (Pack of 1)Verified Purchase
Arrived on time, packaged well. Now about the flavor... I usually purchase one of ON's chocolate varieties, but I had been wanting to try something new. Since they don't carry the 1 lb. size at my local GNC, Amazon to the rescue! To me, the Vanilla Ice Cream has a very strong artificially sweet taste, probably due to the sucralose. Double Rich Chocolate, one of my favs, does not contain sucralose. Well, my last 5 lb. tub didn't; maybe that's changed! Double Rich Choc Ingredients: Protein Blend (Whey Protein Isolates, Whey Protein Concentrate, Whey Peptides), Cocoa (Processed with Alkali), Lecithin, Natural and Artificial Flavors, Acesulfame Potassium, Aminogen, Lactase. In any case, I add my protein powder to a shake with spinach and kale, so the taste is quite muted. Used in this manner, the Vanilla Ice Cream flavor was fine; greens cut the sweetness perfectly! However, when I mixed it into plain Greek yogurt, all I could taste was an overwhelming dose of artificial sweetener! That said, I won't repurchase this flavor. Even though I liked it in the green shake, which is how I typically consume protein powder, I'm not thrilled about the addition of sucralose. Can't imagine how sickeningly sweet this would taste for those who mix with just water, almond milk, etc. Yikes! Nope, this one requires considerable disguising, IMO.
